	keywords = {accessibility, automatic validation tools, transparency},
	annote = {The authors analyzed four different web accessibility evaluation tools (Mauve ++, WAVE, AChecker, Qualweb) for transparency, i.e. giving users a clear understanding of how each tool works. Of the four, they found Mauve++ and Qualweb were the clearest on both what is being evaluated and what the results are. In the background section, the authors note that most accessibility reviews use more than one tool.}
